[02:09:22] *** Joins: nullstrin (~nullstrin@cermak.nullstring.io)
[02:09:57] <nullstrin> I am trying to get pacman installed on wsl, it's stuck on 'Locally signing key'
[02:10:22] <nullstrin> any suggestions?
[02:22:07] <WntrMute> use the windows installer ...
[02:22:59] <nullstrin> windows installer?
[02:23:13] <nullstrin> hrm
[02:23:24] <nullstrin> anyway, looks like it didn't matter afterall
[02:23:25] <nullstrin> it's working fine
[02:24:19] <WntrMute> https://devkitpro.org/wiki/Getting_Started
[02:25:12] <WntrMute> https://github.com/devkitPro/installer/releases/latest
[02:25:35] <nullstrin> On Unix-like platforms such as Linux/macOS/WSL, there's devkitPro pacman.
[02:25:40] <nullstrin> says it supports wsl
[02:25:52] <nullstrin> and anyway it's working fine apparently
[02:26:16] <WntrMute> meh
[02:26:53] *** yellows8 sets mode: +oo WntrMute fincs
[02:28:17] <WntrMute> WSL is awkward, we prefer windows users to use the windows binaries
[02:31:09] <nullstrin> I'll take my chances for now. Thanks though.
[02:32:19] <WntrMute> why?
[02:32:36] <WntrMute> why did you install on WSL in the first place?
[02:33:55] <nullstrin> Because I use wsl quite frequently and then went to the wiki page and saw it was mentioned.
[02:34:23] <WntrMute> what's your use case for WSL generally?
[02:35:38] <nullstrin> nothing that particular, just running random linux apps on windows.. 
